You can almost certainly tell the interests and inclinations of a person by analyzing the character of their home. These days, a lot of people in Lagos opt for a home with a modern touch, adorned with contemporary decor elements that propel the home character, giving it a grand demeanour. More people are abandoning the plaid and floral sofa, heavy drapery and 50’s style decorating into the new, clean and bold.

The Tango unit is a reflection of the urban taste trend which captures the essence of city living with youthful flair and pace. The spaces are awash with au courant decor pieces, giving a distinct character to this lovely 2-bedroom home. This 120sqm apartment is zoned for privacy with two standard size bedrooms all ensuite; all generously laid out on one floor.

&nbsp;

[caption id="attachment_48331" align="alignnone" width="569"]<a href="https://castles.com.ng/2-bedroom-apartment-design-scheme-1/1-80/" rel="attachment wp-att-48331"><img class=" wp-image-48331" src="https://castles.com.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-12-280x300.jpg" alt="" width="569" height="607" /></a>                                                                DESIGN SCHEME 1<br />                                                                  (FLOOR PLAN)<br />                                                House Type – 2 Bedroom Apartment[/caption]

&nbsp;

A shaded architectural plan of the home layout allows us to fully appreciate the spatial arrangement and functional composition (viewing from the top). From this view, we can see it’s composed of a generous living area and kitchen, spacious en suite bedrooms, and a visitor’s toilet neatly tucked into a corner.

[caption id="attachment_48330" align="alignnone" width="586"]<a href="https://castles.com.ng/2-bedroom-apartment-design-scheme-1/2-77/" rel="attachment wp-att-48330"><img class=" wp-image-48330" src="https://castles.com.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-12-300x203.jpg" alt="" width="586" height="396" /></a> <br />                                           DESIGN SCHEME 1<br />                                      (3D “CUTPLANE” VIEW)<br />                            House Type – 2 Bedroom Apartment[/caption]

[read more="Click here to Read More" less="Read Less"]<b></b>

&nbsp;

The rendered 3D floor plan visually expresses the needed realistic view of the spaces to fully admire the choice of components and its composition.

[caption id="attachment_48329" align="alignnone" width="578"]<a href="https://castles.com.ng/2-bedroom-apartment-design-scheme-1/3-75/" rel="attachment wp-att-48329"><img class=" wp-image-48329" src="https://castles.com.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-10-300x203.jpg" alt="" width="578" height="391" /></a>                                       DESIGN SCHEME 1<br />                             (3D “CUTPLANE” VIEW)<br />                 House Type – 2 Bedroom Apartment[/caption]

&nbsp;

A closer look reveals the intricacies of this neat layout. With bold patterns toned down with minimalistic white seating in the living room, it is an oasis of freshness and vibrancy. The parquet floors of the bedrooms are simply exquisite and the plush centre rugs with unique stripes and textures are divine.

[caption id="attachment_48328" align="alignnone" width="661"]<a href="https://castles.com.ng/2-bedroom-apartment-design-scheme-1/4-59/" rel="attachment wp-att-48328"><img class=" wp-image-48328" src="https://castles.com.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-9-300x250.jpg" alt="" width="661" height="551" /></a> White walls matched with the boiserie are a good combo which goes quite well with the monochrome checkered centre rug and colourful throw pillows: the atmosphere here breathes calmness and freshness. The boiserie is minimalist and appeals to the modern design lover. The display cubbies of the water dispenser niche and the simple line of wood console and mirror is a good way to keep things nifty and clean without overdoing it.[/caption]

